window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>Following the loss of most of his colleagues in a violent ambush, Kenton has become Lord Mastrell of the few remaining Sand Masters, magicians who can manipulate sand to do their bidding. With the ruling council poised against him, the hot-headed Kenton must become a diplomat to have any hope of preventing the eradication of his people forever. However, there’s another complication: assassins are coming for him from all directions, and Kenton’s only true ally is Khriss, a visitor from the other side of the planet who has an agenda of her own to pursue.</p> <p><i>White Sand, Volume 2</i> continues the <i>New York Times</i> best-selling series of graphic novel adaptations, bringing a crucial chapter of Brandon Sanderson’s <i>Cosmere </i>to life in GraphicAudio.</p> <p>Performed by Terence Aselford, Alexander Strain, Dawn Ursula, Bradley Smith, Yasmin Tuazon, Jason B McIntosh, Scott McCormick, Frank Britton, KenYatta Rogers, Mort Shelby, Rose Elizabeth Supan, Duyen Washington, Eric Messner, Joe Mallon, Jonathon Church, Paul Reisman, Steve Wannall, Ken Jackson, Alejandro Ruiz, Michael John Casey, James Lewis, Jonathan Feuer, Colleen Delany, Nick DePinto, Tim Carlin, Matthew Bassett, Andy Brownstein, Nanna Ingvarsson, Holly Vagley, Elizabeth Jernigan, Joy Jones, Alyssa Wilmoth, Chris Davenport.</p>"; 
